# Git Hygiene

Before committing or creating a PR:

- Inspect `git status --short` and include only files related to the requested change.
- Keep local/dev-only changes out of feature commits unless explicitly requested.
- Do not commit `.DS_Store`; if tracked, remove from Git with `git rm --cached`.
- Treat accidental `package-lock.json` churn as unrelated unless dependency changes were intentional.
- Preserve local ngrok/development environment changes unless the user explicitly asks to alter them.
- Mention any unrelated dirty files left in the working tree.
